Two men, Nura Usman and Adamu Dauda, have been remanded in a correctional facility for allegedly defecating in a mosque. They were remanded on Thursday by a Shariâ€™a Court in Magajin Gari, Kaduna State. The two men, Nura Usman and Adamu Dauda were charged with public nuisance and inciting violence by the police. Malam Rilwanu Kyaudai, the judge, adjourned the case for the police to present witnesses on 28th April, 2022. Inspector Ibrahim Shuaibu, the prosecution counsel, explained that the two accused persons, Usman and Dauda were handed over to the Tudun Wada Police Station on April 11 by members of the community. According to the prosecution counsel, Nura Usman was around 2pm caught defecating in a mosque on Alkalawa Road, Tudun Wada, Kaduna. Inspector Ibrahim Shuaibu also alleged that Adamu Dauda, the second defendant, promised to give Nura Usman N20,000 to defecate in the mosque.